         UPDATED=20031125
           SHORT="An ipv6 advertising router daemon"
cat << EOF
The router advertisement daemon (radvd) is run by Linux or BSD systems
acting as IPv6 routers. It sends Router Advertisement messages, specified
by RFC 2461, to a local Ethernet LAN periodically and when requested by
a node sending a Router Solicitation message. These messages are required
for IPv6 stateless autoconfiguration.
EOF
